Iteration: 1 - Login
Request Description
### Login The `POST` request is used to authenticate and login to the QuizApp. **Request Body** - `username` (text, required): The username of the user. - `password` (text, required): The password of the user. **Response** - `code` (number): The status code of the response. - `status` (string): The status of the response. - `message` (string): Any additional message related to the response. - `data` (object): The data object containing the access token, refresh token, and password type. - `access_token` (string): The access token for the authenticated user. - `refresh_token` (string): The refresh token for the authenticated user. - `password_type` (string): The type of password used for authentication. An example of a successful response: ``` json { "code": 0, "status": "", "message": "", "data": { "access_token": "", "refresh_token": "", "password_type": "" } } ```

Iteration: 1 - Post Quiz Data
Request Description
The `POST /categories/questions` endpoint is used to add new questions to specific categories. The request should include a payload in the raw request body type with the `quiz_data` field containing an array of objects, each representing a category and its associated question data. ### Request Payload - `quiz_data` (array of objects) - `category` (string): The category to which the question belongs. - `question_data` (array of objects) - `question_text` (string): The text of the question. - `question_type` (string): The type of the question. - `options` (object) - `answer` (string): The correct answer to the question. - `other_options` (array): An array of other options for the question. ### Response The endpoint returns a status code of 201 upon successful creation of the questions. The response body is in JSON format with the following fields: - `code` (number): The status code of the response. - `status` (string): The status of the response. - `message` (string): A message regarding the response. #### Example Response ``` json { "code": 0, "status": "", "message": "" } ```

Iteration: 1 - Login
Request Description
### Login The `POST` request is used to authenticate and login to the QuizApp. **Request Body** - `username` (text, required): The username of the user. - `password` (text, required): The password of the user. **Response** - `code` (number): The status code of the response. - `status` (string): The status of the response. - `message` (string): Any additional message related to the response. - `data` (object): The data object containing the access token, refresh token, and password type. - `access_token` (string): The access token for the authenticated user. - `refresh_token` (string): The refresh token for the authenticated user. - `password_type` (string): The type of password used for authentication. An example of a successful response: ``` json { "code": 0, "status": "", "message": "", "data": { "access_token": "", "refresh_token": "", "password_type": "" } } ```

Iteration: 1 - Post Quiz Data
Request Description
The `POST /categories/questions` endpoint is used to add new questions to specific categories. The request should include a payload in the raw request body type with the `quiz_data` field containing an array of objects, each representing a category and its associated question data. ### Request Payload - `quiz_data` (array of objects) - `category` (string): The category to which the question belongs. - `question_data` (array of objects) - `question_text` (string): The text of the question. - `question_type` (string): The type of the question. - `options` (object) - `answer` (string): The correct answer to the question. - `other_options` (array): An array of other options for the question. ### Response The endpoint returns a status code of 201 upon successful creation of the questions. The response body is in JSON format with the following fields: - `code` (number): The status code of the response. - `status` (string): The status of the response. - `message` (string): A message regarding the response. #### Example Response ``` json { "code": 0, "status": "", "message": "" } ```

Iteration: 1 - Post Quiz Data
Request Description
The `POST /categories/questions` endpoint is used to add new questions to specific categories. The request should include a payload in the raw request body type with the `quiz_data` field containing an array of objects, each representing a category and its associated question data. ### Request Payload - `quiz_data` (array of objects) - `category` (string): The category to which the question belongs. - `question_data` (array of objects) - `question_text` (string): The text of the question. - `question_type` (string): The type of the question. - `options` (object) - `answer` (string): The correct answer to the question. - `other_options` (array): An array of other options for the question. ### Response The endpoint returns a status code of 201 upon successful creation of the questions. The response body is in JSON format with the following fields: - `code` (number): The status code of the response. - `status` (string): The status of the response. - `message` (string): A message regarding the response. #### Example Response ``` json { "code": 0, "status": "", "message": "" } ```
